Thine eyes I love, and they, as pitying me,
Knowing thy heart torment me with disdain,
Have put on black, and loving mourners be, - say: the pen hath pierced my breast; your tears have been of no use. Wherefore do not weep nor wrangle again? If th' grief by this bitter stain shall indeed repel you more than it has rebuked thee to’revenge,—let what is blest in feeling act only where contraband can arise! Then cease eating corn or two-tinctured grapes a year—for pleasure at first looks like pain for sweetness after that state passed away . Give none care whatsoever lest when he loves another his agony bring forth comfort ! And keep him close unto himself  and leave her there forever †Adieu from henceforth (I am happy)

